Explain WHATWG.
WHATWG stands for Web HyperText Application Technology Working Group which is an organization 
that develops and also maintains the HTML and API for web applications.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is an API in HTML5?
API stands for Application Programming Interfaces and is a way to create applications.
They use pre-built components. Using the available APIs, developers can integrate the features into their websites
